Package: bash
Section: shells
Essential: yes
Priority: required
Architecture: ARCH
Depends: libc (>= 1.1.8), ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: the Bourne Again SHell
 Bash is the GNU Project's shell. Bash is the Bourne Again SHell.
 .
 Bash is an sh-compatible shell that incorporates useful features
 from the Korn shell (ksh) and C shell (csh).
 .
 It is intended to conform to the IEEE POSIX P1003.2/ISO 9945.2
 Shell and Tools standard. It offers functional improvements over
 sh for both programming and interactive use.

Package: bash-dev
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Architecture: ARCH
Depends: bash (= ${binary:Version})
Description: Development headers for bash
 This package provides development headers and pkgconfig data for
 bash.

Package: bash-doc
Section: doc
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Recommends: man-db
Depends: bash (= ${binary:Version})
Description: documentation for bash
 This package provides info and man pages for bash.
